{"type":"message","id":"a91af41b","parentId":"ae731781","timestamp":"2026-02-15T17:39:01.490Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reflecting on Completion**\n\nI've finally synthesized the complete picture. The key bottleneck is in `dmarket_api.py`, specifically `_sign_request`, due to the use of `nacl.signing.SigningKey`. I am now looking at the other modules.\n\n\n**Revising Bottlenecks**\n\nI've clarified the core performance bottleneck: the repeated instantiation of `nacl.signing.SigningKey` within `_sign_request`. Now, I've outlined a Rust extension strategy using `pyo3` to manage the key state efficiently. I'm focusing on creating a streamlined `sign` function for the wrapper.\n\n\n**Investigating Dependencies**\n\nI've shifted focus to dependencies. First, I've confirmed that the primary bottleneck stems from frequent `SigningKey` instantiation. Next, I'm examining the `pre-commit-config.yaml` for module 2, which is quite robust. I've noted the absence of shell linters. Also, in the third module, I'm now evaluating the Redis setup: `redis` library is installed, but it doesn't mean vector search will work.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771177141490_17","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docker-compose.yml"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":87066,"output":632,"cacheRead":76281,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87698,"cost":{"input":0.17413199999999998,"output":0.0075840000000000005,"cacheRead":0.015256200000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1969722}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771177129382}}
